The paper deals with the approximability of a classic NP-hard optimization problem in graphs, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories related to graph theory and algorithms. The focus on the minimum degree greedy algorithm and the design of advice for it suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The analysis of approximation ratios and the study of the problem on specific classes of graphs suggest that it could also belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
